OL,3,CD-Day 80 The Last Veterans: Harry
OL,4,CGarthwaite
OL,6,F"Sure enough the tannoy came on and
OL,7,Fsaid the invasion had started, a
OL,8,Fbridgehead had been formed and
OL,9,Feverything was going to plan. We were
OL,10,Fleaving on D-Day.
OL,12,F"During the weeks beforehand we had
OL,13,Fseen an awful lot of traffic (on the
OL,14,FSouth coast). Convoys hiding in woods.
OL,15,FThere was a lot of landing craft about.
OL,17,F"We were flying up and down that coast
OL,18,Ffor a while before D-Day. Taking
OL,19,Fofficers to various outside units.
OL,21,F"Everyone was expecting an invasion."
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/6
