OL,3,CD-Day 80 The Last Veterans: Harry
OL,4,CGarthwaite
OL,6,F"That's why it was isolated. No phone
OL,7,Fcalls in and out. You couldn't get out
OL,8,Fof the camp. Once you got in you were
OL,9,Fstuck. They said 'You can't go until
OL,10,Fthey have all gone.'
OL,12,F"So we sat in the mess and drank
OL,13,Fcoffee until they had gone."
OL,15,FAbout four days later Mr Garthwaite
OL,16,Fbegan flying officers directly to the
OL,17,FNormandy bridgehead and bringing
OL,18,Fwalking wounded back to RAF Tangmere
OL,19,Fin Sussex where ambulances were
OL,20,Fwaiting for them.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/6
